transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling customer service.

Speaker 2: I can help you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I was looking for actually customer service.

Speaker 2: Did I reach the wrong line?

Speaker 1: No, this is customer service.

Speaker 2: Oh, okay. Hey, I was on the line here and got some e-mail,

Speaker 1: and I lost everything on my desktop computer.

Speaker 2: And what I did was I had some of this regular school blue,

Speaker 1: and I went to order some new stuff.

Speaker 2: And the new AGV, and she said, oh, no, you can't just order it right online like you did.

Speaker 1: You have to, you know, go back and do it another way.

Speaker 2: So you guys, can you look at my phone?

Speaker 1: Yeah, can you look at my phone number for me?

Speaker 2: Yes, can I have your phone number, please?

Speaker 1: It's John Bohecker.

Speaker 2: It's October the 8th, 1940.

Speaker 1: Thank you, John.

Speaker 2: Are you still on Hapsway?

Speaker 1: Yes, 1002 Hapsway.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: You want to get the AGV, how many pills, 10, 25, or 40?

Speaker 2: Well, let's see, they were going to send it to me, so I don't know what happened.

Speaker 1: See, they said to return the old one that I got from them, and I lost all the information

Speaker 2: on where to send it and everything like that.

Speaker 1: But anyway, they said, we're going to send you an email, and I lost everything on here.

Speaker 2: And I had the old pills, I ordered them, and she said, no, no, no, you can't just order them

Speaker 1: like you do normally over the phone, because you got the regular stuff.

Speaker 2: So she said, whatever's left in there, send back to us.

Speaker 1: And they left an email, and I lost everything on there on my desktop.

Speaker 2: And then she said, yeah.

Speaker 1: So that's what was happening.

Speaker 2: Okay, I'm going to re-send you the email that you received.

Speaker 1: Oh, good, okay.

Speaker 2: Okay, I re-send the email, now you should have it.

Speaker 1: Yeah, and then, oh, let me see if I do, hold on a second.

Speaker 2: Hold on. Sometimes it'll take a while to get through.

Speaker 1: Oh, nope, got it, okay.

Speaker 2: Okay. Returned, very good.

Speaker 1: And then she said, the woman I was talking to said, we're going to send you some of the new.

Speaker 2: And the 100 type, 100MG, and I don't know if she was going to send it

Speaker 1: or if she said to reorder it or whatever.

Speaker 2: Okay, send that one back first, and then call back.

Speaker 1: Save the tracking number, because we need the tracking number.

Speaker 2: Okay. You said you have a tracking number?

Speaker 1: No, you give us the tracking number.

Speaker 2: Call us with the tracking number when you send it back so we can get you the AGB.

Speaker 1: Okay, good.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Appreciate that.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.

Speaker 1: Have a good day.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Okay, if you want to talk to Abby, Abby, you want to talk to her?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right, less than three months.
